Package: mmirestriktor
Title: Informative Hypothesis Testing Web Applications and Tools
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mackson", "Ncube", , "macksonncube.stats@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("mightymetrika, LLC", role = c("cph", "fnd"))
  )
Description: Informative hypothesis testing allows researchers to explicitly
    model their expectations regarding the relationships among parameters,
    offering enhanced statistical power compared to traditional methods. An
    important software tool for informative hypothesis testing is 'restriktor'.
    The 'mmirestriktor' package provides 'shiny' web applications to implement
    some of the basic functionality of the 'restriktor' package; moreover,
    'mmirestriktor' provides development tools for building 'shiny' web
    applications on top of the 'restriktor' informative hypothesis testing
    capabilities. The mmirestriktor() function launches a shiny web application
    for fitting and analyzing models with constraints. The FbarCards() function
    launches a 'shiny' application for a card game designed to build intuition
    about informative hypothesis testing. The iht_interpreter() function helps
    interpret informative hypothesis testing results based on guidelines
    presented in Vanbrabant and Rosseel (2020) <doi:10.4324/9780429273872-14>.
